    "headline": "Gartner raises profit forecast on strong AI service demand",
    "summary": "Gartner on Tuesday raised its annual profit forecast driven by steady demand for its ‌research and advisory services, as companies continue ‌to assess technology upgrades and AI adoption plans. Gartner's research has ​become critical in technology planning and vendor evaluation processes across a wide range of industries, supported by its large data sets and domain expertise. It ‌now expects 2026 ⁠adjusted earnings at $13.25 per share, compared to analysts' average estimate of $13.16 per share, ⁠according to data compiled by LSEG.",
